This paper discusses the learnability bias in natural language acquisition, which is a topic related to computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also investigates the behavior of artificial neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the distribution of data, which is relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC).
